abstract: NASHVILLE, July 13--Leading from start to finish and never faltering during four days of record high temperatures, Amy Alcott won the 35th annual United States Women's Open golf championship by nine strokes today with a record score of 280, four under par for the 72 holes at the Richland Country Club.

abstract: NASHVILLE, July 11--Amy Alcott continued to thrive despite extreme heat today as she shot her second straight one-under-par round of 70 and took sole possession of the lead at 140 halfway through the 35th annual United States Women's Open golf championship.

abstract: NASHVILLE, July 10--Amy Alcott picked up ice now and then to overcome the swelling and numbness in her hands that developed as temperatures soared to 103 degrees on the unshaded fairways and greens of the Richland Country Club course today.
